RACE.FOOTNOTES: AZUNIA set the pace along the rail and lead all around, merry go round, to triumph in the end. MOR PEANUTS stalked the pace throughout the course while two wide and held on gamely to the place prize in the end. WAVING BYE stalked the pace in the three path into the turn and was best for show in the end. FAST TRACK chased the trio of rivals from the inside throughout the course and was no threat. PHUNK reared up at the start, then chased the pace in last position throughout and was no threat.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 72. Allowance Purse 33500. (PLUS UP TO $1,675 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EAGLE EXPRESS gradually took command from the fence after the first eighth of a mile, opened a measured, well-rated advantage through the turn, cleared the field in upper stretch and held the closer safe at the wire. DIAMONDS N ACES rated between horses off the pace to the head of the lane, split horses and dug in gamely to be closing well late in the drive. CANDY BEE stalked the leaders from the fence in a three horse second flight duel, cut the corner to challenge turning for home and finished evenly along the rail for the show. SENORITA BROOKE took the early lead from the gate, settled in to press the pace for a half mile and weakened in the stretch. LEXINGTON DIVA raced five wide from the back of the field through the turn and passed a tiring rival late. VOODOO MISTRESS chased the pacesetters from three wide in the second flight and flattened out in upper stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 16000. (PLUS UP TO $800 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FORT HOOD rushed up in the first furlong to out bid inner rivals and led the way down the backstretch and throughout the turn and was kept to task till the end. MORO OUTLAW vied for the lead while two wide, then pressed the pace into the turn, was in a strong rally but could not catch the leader in the stretch and needed more. SILVER AND GOLD was urging down the backstretch behind the field while two wide, was moving up on the turn to rally in the stretch and closed gamely for third place. MR. NIGHTBLINGER vied for the lead from the four path, then settled rallied on the turn but came up evenly in the stretch. INFINITE MORO showed brief speed early then dropped back along the inside down the remainder of the backstretch, made a mild bid in the early stretch and was no threat. RED BIRD'S STORM vied for the lead while three wide then settled back and continued to chase the pace down the back stretch then flattened out on the turn and was no threat.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 91. Allowance Purse 33500. (PLUS UP TO $6,700 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR TEXAS BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. RACE.FOOTNOTES: COSMO chased the pace down the backstretch while two wide, then rallied in the early stretch to move up and vie for the lead while five wide, drifted in then dueled with an inner foe and was up at the wire. MISTER K was in a hard drive to vie for the lead from the inside throughout the first three quarters, then inched away in the late stretch to duel with an outer rival and hung in the end. FIRST AVENUE raced behind the field down the backstretch, then bid on the turn to rally in the late stretch and closed strong and was up for the show prize. MALIBU S S chased the trio into the turn from the inside, then dug in gamely in the early stretch to vie between rivals, was taken up, angled out five wide to re bid but it wasn't enough in the end. TAPISTAR vied for the lead with two inner rivals down the backstretch and throughout the turn, continued to menace gamelty down stretch then gave way in the end. GRAPNEL vied for the lead between rivals throughout the course then gave way in late stretch. There was a STEWARD'S INQUIRY and JOCKEY'S OBJECTION following the race. The rider of MALIBU S S claimed foul against the rider of COSMO for interference in late stretch. After reviewing the replay, COSMO was disqualified and placed fourth.

BILLY YANK stalked the pace from the rail to the quarter pole while saving all the ground and failed to mount a rally in the lane. GIST slow early to trail the field to the quarter pole and showed late interest making up ground in the stretch. DIRT BIKE SLADE trailed most of the way as a non-factor. WEST TEXAS BOB pressed the pace for a half mile and came up empty tiring through the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOLY EMPEROR set the pace through the first turn, settled just off the pace pressing rival down the backstretch, re-engaged into the far turn, took command shaking off his pace rival in upper stretch and finished gamely holding the runner-up safe.
